  "body": "Passing `--show-labels` to the following `kubectl get` commands do not make a difference, because the printer is not the table printer:\r\n\r\n- `kubectl get pods -o=yaml --show-labels`\r\n- `kubectl get pods -o=json --show-labels`\r\n- `kubectl get pods -o=name --show-labels`\r\n- ...\r\n\r\nCurrent behavior is that the `--show-labels` simply doesn\u2019t make a difference since it\u2019s not applicable.\r\n\r\nIn these cases, we must error out with a message like _\u201c--show-labels option cannot be used with yaml printer\u201d_.\r\n\r\nI think it\u2019s sane to error out when usage of a flag is always going to be incompatible in the presence (or some values\u2013) of certain flags.\r\n\r\nA caveat is that `--show-labels` is valid in the context of `-o=wide` or `-o=custom-columns=...` options.\r\n\r\n/sig cli\r\n/kind bug\r\nVersion: kubectl v1.8.2",
